cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on device-to-device communication links and proposes a game model to allocate resources among them. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes a noncooperative game model to address the resource allocation problem among the D2D links. This falls under the scope of computer science and game theory.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the physical channel access issue in D2D communication links and proposes a pricing strategy to maximize the total D2D throughput. This falls under the scope of information theory.
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a game model to allocate resources among the D2D links, which can be seen as a social network. This falls under the scope of social and information networks.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the performance of overlay D2D communication links, which can be used for multimedia transmission. This falls under the scope of multimedia.
